==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heinous
<hw>Hei"nous</hw> <pr>(h⟦amac⟧"n⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>ha⟦ium⟧nos</ets> hateful, F. <ets>haineux</ets>, fr. OF.
<ets>ha⟦ium⟧ne</ets> hate, F. <ets>haine</ets>, fr. <ets>ha⟦ium⟧r</ets>
to hate; of German origin. See <er>Hate</er>.]</ety> <def>Hateful;
hatefully bad; flagrant; odious; atrocious; giving great offense; --
applied to deeds or to character.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It were most <qex>heinous</qex> and accursed sacrilege.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How <qex>heinous</qex> had the fact been, how deserving⟦br⟧
Contempt!</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Monstrous; flagrant; flagitious;
atrocious.</syn></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Hei"nous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Hei"nous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>heinousness</ent>⟦br⟧
